{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DTMuMyoP8q2RZCktE73dhu","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good. All fixes applied. Here's the summary:\n\n---\n\n**Review complete for story 8-7 (Rust OTLP Instrumentation).**\n\n**Files modified:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/templates/otlp/rust.md` -- fixed transport protocol mismatch and added missing env vars\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/otlp.test.ts` -- added 4 direct tests for `ensureEndpointEnvVar`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-7-rust-otlp-instrumentation.md` -- status updated to `verifying`\n\n**Results:**\n- 3014 tests pass, 0 failures, 0 regressions\n- otlp.ts: 100% statement coverage (was 98.77%)\n- Overall: 97.05% (target: 90%) -- PASS\n- All 123 files above 80% per-file floor -- PASS\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n\n- **HIGH: Transport/port mismatch in `templates/otlp/rust.md`** -- The Rust setup code used `.with_tonic()` (gRPC, port 4317) while the env var and `.env.codeharness` write `http://localhost:4318` (HTTP). Sending gRPC to an HTTP endpoint would fail at runtime. Fixed by changing to `.with_http()` and aligning the default fallback to port 4318.\n- **MEDIUM: Missing OTEL exporter env vars in `templates/otlp/rust.md`** -- The template omitted `OTEL_TRACES_EXPORTER`, `OTEL_METRICS_EXPORTER`, `OTEL_LOGS_EXPORTER` which are present in both nodejs.md and python.md. Fixed by adding them.\n- **MEDIUM: `ensureEndpointEnvVar` had two uncovered branches** -- The \"update existing endpoint\" path (line 298) and \"create new file\" path (line 304) were never directly tested. Fixed by adding 4 direct unit tests.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority):**\n\n- **LOW: Code duplication between `ensureServiceNameEnvVar` and `ensureEndpointEnvVar`** -- Both functions share identical file read/write/update logic. Could be refactored to a generic `ensureEnvVar(projectDir, key, value)` helper. Not worth changing now since it's only two functions and the pattern is stable.\n- **LOW: `RUST_OTLP_PACKAGES` not exported** -- Unlike `WEB_OTLP_PACKAGES` and `AGENT_OTLP_PACKAGES_*`, the install package arrays (`NODE_OTLP_PACKAGES`, `PYTHON_OTLP_PACKAGES`, `RUST_OTLP_PACKAGES`) are not exported. Consistent but could be cleaner if tests verified against the constant directly.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n\n- Branch coverage for `ensureEndpointEnvVar` is now covered. Remaining uncovered branches in otlp.ts are in `instrumentProject` output message paths (json mode suppression) which are cosmetic.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n\n- None for this story. The implementation follows established patterns correctly.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af305a10f955d5a17 (use SendMessage with to: 'af305a10f955d5a17' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 55804\ntool_uses: 36\nduration_ms: 236350</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ccb5b6c6-90ec-46ee-9865-cad53e4d258b","uuid":"667dd419-93ac-4f01-bbc7-584f76815804","timestamp":"2026-03-23T07:59:15.785Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-7-rust-otlp-instrumentation.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief description)\n- Code quality issues found but NOT fixed 