{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01JDBAWThvt9yyDeCigVxwhv","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01HYJc15azR4GDqWZst4GD8B","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","old_string":"- **Sprint-status.yaml corruption:** The dev-story agent overwrote sprint-status.yaml with placeholder content. Had to restore from git and manually set status to `review`.","new_string":"- **Sprint-status.yaml corruption:** The dev-story agent overwrote sprint-status.yaml with placeholder content. Had to restore from git and manually set status to `review`.\n\n### 8-7-rust-otlp-instrumentation — code-review (2026-03-23T12:00Z)\n\n- **HIGH: Transport/port mismatch in `templates/otlp/rust.md`** — Template used `.with_tonic()` (gRPC, port 4317) while env var writes `http://localhost:4318` (HTTP). Would fail at runtime. Fixed by changing to `.with_http()`.\n- **MEDIUM: Missing OTEL exporter env vars in `templates/otlp/rust.md`** — Template omitted `OTEL_TRACES_EXPORTER`, `OTEL_METRICS_EXPORTER`, `OTEL_LOGS_EXPORTER`. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM: `ensureEndpointEnvVar` had two uncovered branches** — \"update existing\" and \"create new file\" paths never directly tested. Fixed by adding 4 unit tests.\n- **LOW (not fixed): Code duplication between `ensureServiceNameEnvVar` and `ensureEndpointEnvVar`** — Could be refactored to a generic `ensureEnvVar()` helper."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":673,"cache_read_input_tokens":40314,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":673},"output_tokens":55,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ccb5b6c6-90ec-46ee-9865-cad53e4d258b","uuid":"9c46b1a0-7a78-4d9b-b5e5-01c7af461a0